caption: This place is amazing. I’m having fajitas right now. This spicy margarita is the best thing to happen this week other than my vaccination

My wife and I have been eyeballing this restaurant. We finally made two Friday's ago. I really wanted a big burrito. The one El Nuevo is serving is almost like 3 pigs in a blanket ( three little burritos). Nothing special. Chips are amazingly fresh and they serve it in a nice little sealed pouch. We have eaten at El Nuevo Mexicano Restaurant a few times over the years, having had it recommended by a friend and it never disappoints. The atmosphere is excellent and the food is tremendous and never disappoints.
They also bring you chips and salsa which was fabulous. Coming from England it was nice to be served hot salsa!
The food was delicious and the drinks from the bar matched well. Parking is a challenge, so leave your time to look for a spot.

I was out with a friend and decided to give this place a try. The dish I ordered was a speciality dish, described as Salmon with mashed potatoes and housemade chipotle sauce. The lack of flavors and heat from chipotle peppers was a major disappointment. The carnitas tacos my friend ordered were dry and the rice and beans were stale. One of the worst experiences at a Mexican restaurant. I would definitely skip their margaritas as they are sugar bombs.
Great place!
I could only finish all my food because I was hungry from hiking for a long day, otherwise I would have had to take the leftovers with me.
Plus about $65 for 4 for 3 dishes and 2 drinks, so good value. We could radically reduce the cost next time because we over-ordered. Open late, plus. Around midnight, we had dinner.
Most evenings, they have plenty of great dishes to choose from and live music and a packed bar. Valet parking in the rear of the house, on Sunset, be careful to park.

We used to spend our day here with all my friends. Last week we ordered some food and it was so delicious. We were all so satisfied because it was so tasty! Food and services were amazing. They have an awesome vegan/vegetarian menu. Highly recommend trying them. Our server was Jonathan and he was extremely professional with great recommendations on everything. Highly recommend checking them out. Delicious food, delicious drinks, and great ambiance.

I recently went here when I heard they had a safe patio for dining. My girlfriend and I really enjoyed every moment! Each table had its own heater and seems far enough away from all the other tables. This is a great Mexican food option in Chicago. In my opinion, it’s probably one of the best options you have in the city. I am from the west coast and have lived in San Diego so I do have high standards when it comes to Mexican food, but I really enjoy this place. It strikes the perfect balance of cozy atmosphere, friendly and attentive service, and good food. Margs are good too!  I would recommend this place as a great go-to weeknight option or casual Friday night dinner if you forgot to make reservations. It’s become my “old reliable” in the Lakeview neighborhood. I can come without a reservation, get a table quickly, and know I will enjoy good food. I really want to like this place. They try so hard to be a basic Mexican restaurant, but they tend to fail so bad for no reason. I made a reservation for four for a Saturday night. An hour later I called to change it to five. Less than an hour after that, they called me back to confirm. Then an hour before our dinner, they called me AGAIN to confirm. Once we arrived, we waited 35 minutes past our reservation for a table. What is the point in making a reservation, much less reconfirming twice, if you make people wait that long?  After seated, our server was rushing us along for our order, presumably to catch up with the schedule. Why were they not pressuring the prior table to move it along instead?  I will never go back. There are too many other basic Tex-Mex places with less hassle than here.

If I could give zero stars, I would. This is easily the worst "Mexican" restaurant I have ever been to, if you even want to call it that. This place is a joke. For the prices, I would expect great food but it was terrible. I ordered the steak burritos and the plate consisted of three burritos that were about three inches, a spoonful of beans, a spoonful of rice, and a spoonful of salad. The price was $19 by the way. A friend ordered the shrimp and their idea of a garnish was alternated bell peppers and bits of parsley around the plate. It looked like a terrible chef was trying to create an elegant plate but failed miserably. Also, the salsa tasted like marinara sauce. I wouldn't recommend this restaurant to anyone. It is not authentic at all. They don't even offer any Mexican drinks such as horchata or jamaica. I suggest going to a place in Pilsen such as Los Comales that has good food and even better prices. The owner should be ashamed of themselves.

Our server made an excellent suggestion that was similar, yet different. So I ordered Enchiladas Crema De Chipotle. We also had guacomole. THE FOOD: The guacamole was a bit of a disappointment. It seemed blender smooth, and didn't have a lot of flavor. The Enchilladas de pollo en mole Verde was excellent. Really tasty, savory and well made. I love the burritos, my girlfriend loved the tacos. The salsa and chips were the best we had in Chicago. Then we received a free flan with hearts in it. What a great completion to an awesome dinner. Thanks

Rafael and the crew were on point with my tables' cocktails and the wonderful dessert served for my birthday. My first visit, but it will not be my last. The Golden Cadillac cocktails were the most. Do yo' thang El Nuevo! Love it! And my dinner was superb as well! Awesome!

I would say the food here is solid Mexican without being overly fancy or tex mex-y. I came here with my book club group. Some of us have allergies and others didn't like spice but the waiter was patient with us and made notes when we asked him to. We got the pitcher of margs - non flavored and they taste really good. I got thr enchiladas of carne asada and they were extremely well made. The portions are huge as well  They have a large patio in the back which they open up in the summer. The tables are made of chicken wire type metal so some things slip through / get stuck in it, ask for a platter in the middle for cutlery.  Overall everything was delicious, including dessert- I didn't think the tres leches cake was very authentic but it was tasty. Total was about 40 each for 4 people.
Great place, sumptuous meals and good service.
The dinner was great, both the veggie meal and the steak burrito we ordered were flavored well. Our meal was highlighted by the attentive and responsive waitstaff.
Excellent vegan choices, not just beans. Creative dishes for vegan and meat eater alike. Excellent service. Guacamole just needed a little more salt.

Terrible customer service!! The "manager" is the real problem! Terrible!! He makes up rules that I have never heard of!! The place was empty  (4 families in there total at 5 pm) and he came over to our table and told us we couldn't have our stroller. Mind you we have a 3 month old who can't sit in a high chair. We were seated already and he made a huge deal about having a stroller.  We walked there and he wanted us to go get our car seat!! We left and will not be back.
Best. Margaritas. Ever. And my creamy chipotle enchiladas made this displaced Californian very happy (and I'm picky about my Mexican food).
This is one of my favorite restaurants in the city. Everyone I have taken here loves it. I especially love the vegetarian menu. So many great choices! Thank you!
(Translated by Google) Really delicious and very nice service, to great Taccos 😋👍😋👍  (Original) Echt super lecker und sehr nette Bedienung, dazu super Taccos 😋👍😋👍
Delicious old school Mexican place.  One of the best Mexican restaurants I've been to.
Solid. Great margaritas and chips & guac!
Great margaritas and food!
Love the (vegan!) fajitas and guacamole is always awesome every time we've been here

Service was slow and uninformed. Sopapillas were crispy and not fluffy at all and they should have been. And are you kidding me with a 3 dollar charge for a side of salsa without  informing your guests? Will not be returning.

Went here with some of our friends. The food was good. However, the service was a bit slow and it was pricey. For four people and 8 beers on a Monday night it was $120 dollars before tip. I don't know about you but when I go to get Mexican food I typically imagine around a 30 to 40 dollar bill for my wife and I. Not 60 plus. Also, they charge you for additional chips and salsa... Wonderful food. Great vegan options. Unique and artistic. You'll be very satisfied

We had two different carne asada s. Both absolutely amazing.
Back patio was great! Service was awesome and food was even better. I got chicken enchiladas which were so good.
Got the vegan flautas delivered through caviar and I just had to hop on here to say they are INCREDIBLE.  I enjoyed every bite.  Thank you for providing a delicious vegan meal.
Ambiance good. Food average. Drinks good. Nowwarm so outside deck and garden better. Great for mini bdays.
Awesome service, great food and quality drinks. Authentic food as well. Highly recommend!
Cadillac margaritas are to die for but they need a better dishwasher as more than one of us found less than perfect dishes.
(Translated by Google) Great Cinco de Mayo margarita special!  (Original) Great Cinco de Mayo margarita special!

Apparently this place has been here for 30 plus years. I'm upset that I only discovered it recently. They have a wonderful vegan section on their menu and my food was outstanding. My parents are meat eaters and loved their food as well. The portions are large. A little pricey but worth it. I will be back.
Service was great, the taco meat was burnt and did not taste good at all.

I had the creamy poblano pepper chicken enchilada special. It was literally the most amazing sauce I've ever tried on enchiladas. I also ordered the guacamole appetizer during happy hour bc it was $2 off. For $8 of guac I didn't get much …
Best Mexican food I've ever had
The food is wonderful! The staff is great! And the magaritas divine. Looking forward to trying them for brunch next!
Best Mexican north of the loop!
(Translated by Google) Very rich food and attention was excellent  (Original) Muy rica la comida y la atención fue exelente
(Translated by Google) Chicken with Mole ... Delicious !!  (Original) Pollo con Mole... Delicious!!
Nice atmosphere, attentive wait staff. The fish tacos I had here were terrible though. Serves me right for ordering seafood in Illinois, but if they're on the menu they should at least be decent.
Cozy atmosphere. Delicious food and margaritas. Great staff.
Solid.  Excellent food and drinks!
High quality Mexican restaurant, excellent service.
Amazing place and great food.
Best Mexican place in Lakeview. We have had almost everything on the menu and never been disappointed. The drinks are generous and delicious. The services is always great.
Food is very good authentic Mexican food service is great will definitely come back
Great food, great service. The best fajita I've had in the city!
Vegan/vegetarian diners will find a lot of options on this menu. The vegan flautas with quinoa and salad are excellent. The customer service is also very good.
Great food and drinks.  Extremely friendly staff.
Very cozy Mexican food spot.  Great food with authentic taste!

(Translated by Google) The food is very good and not like in all the restaurants that a dish has to have rice and beans, these are ingenious dishes and with a great flavor.  (Original) La comida es muy buena y no como en todos los restaurantes que un platillo tiene que tener arroz y frijoles, estos son platillos ingeniosos y con un gran sabor.
Food and service were great. A little out of the way from where we were, hotel near Midway, but worth the trek. Alcoholic drinks pricing is a little strange.
Great veg options.

I came here with a group of four on May 5. The staff were so friendly and took time to ensure that we were happy, comfortable, and our needs were met. They even took time to get to know us and chat, even on such a busy day. The food was amazing and incredibly flavorful. The margaritas tasted great and had a good balance. The space is small, so you have to be careful moving around, but it's cozy and we were fortunate to be seated in the back where it was a little roomier. This is one of the best Mexican restaurants I've been to in a long time and I plan on going back.
Your standard awesome neighborhood sit down Mexican restaurant.
This place is excellent. There's tons of options that all taste great. The service was prompt and the food came out super fast. A must try Mexican place in the Lakeview area
Good atmosphere, mediocre service and food
Outstanding service and great food.
Great place
Some of the best Mexican food around and the wait staff is superb!!
Was passing this place while looking for for somewhere else. Couldn't find the intended restaurant and was extremely happy El Nuevo ended up being dinner
Fabulous food for a vegetarian and a meat eater, great margaritas and excellent chips!
The service is really good and the food is as well. It's too bad I don't live in Chicago or else I'd definitely go back.
Good food in a nice location. The atmosphere and service were great.

Walked in on a Tuesday and no problem getting a table for two. Hostess and waiter were very friendly. Margs are excellent and there is a good selection. Guacamole is fantastic and enchiladas came out really quick and were fantastic. Will definitely be back!

The food was very good, although some may find it a bit on the spicy side! The wait staff was attentive, and the space is very nice - the outdoor patio is lovely. However, the prices were very high for the quality of food offered. There is …
Simple and delicious, but the menu had a few fancier platas as well. Better than normal wine selection, too.
Delicious food in good service
Was on vacation in chicago and found This place bye accident im glade i did cuz the food is just outstanding and the server was very good... Will defently come back here
Amazing, authentic Mexican cuisine in a charming atmosphere. The service is spot on, there when needed but not hovering. Try the Golden Cadillac Margaritas.  You won't  be disappointed
great atmosphere, friendly staff. just came for margaritas, which were good but they were not very strong.

Best Mexican restaurant in the neighborhood. Their seafood is very fresh and they always have unique specials that you won't find at other restaurants. I recommend this place to anyone looking for some tasty Mexican food.
One of the best meals ive had.  pollo molé👍👍.. 11$ margs are pricey but they are so damn good

This is a safe approach to Mexican food in a more upscale setting. It's clear this restaurants caters to a specific clientele, they're not trying to win over people who actually enjoy authentic Mexican food regularly. But! The food is not bad, it's pretty good, just seems to be something a little off about it. They also did try very hard in at least making the place look authentic, adorned with Mexican art and other knick knacks, in  brick wall facade. You could always come in and drink a whole bunch of margaritas!

My favorite Mexican place in Chicago, and I'm a bit selective when it comes to Mexican. Great service, delicious salsa that has a tiny kick, very good margaritas, and excellent food. Bonus point for presentation. Drinks are a bit pricey for a Mexican place, but overall a fantastic restaurant

I came here for a weekday lunch on a day off so it was much quieter than usual I suspect. The service was friendly and fast. I had a chicken quesadilla with guac and it was delicious.  The pulled chicken with seasonings really hit the spot!

Absolutely authentically delicious- I enjoyed this place so much. We ordered pitchers of margaritas on the back patio and quietly closed the place down. Service was impeccable- our server brought ice, extra tortillas, refills before we even noticed we needed anything. I would highly recommend the steak fajitas- which include a lovely little platter of guacamole, sour cream, cheeses, and fabulously spicy chunky salsa. Comfortable little establishment to get your Mexican fix.

the food is alright, and the margaritas are terrible. they taste non alcoholic.. 26$ for a pitcher of strawberry slushy. service is horrible, bunch of cocky workers who dont have change for parking meters for customers. never will i return, or recommend this place to anyone. its a rip off. >:)

5 stars can easily go to El Nuevo!  Hands down my favorite Mexican restaurant in Chicago, talk about quality food and great service.  It is the cutest little spot with delicious food and strong margaritas!  You have to ask for the warm salsa when they bring out the chips, it is out of this world and the shrimp tacos (not always on the menu but always available) are the excellent.  I am yet to have had a bad experience at El Nuevo.
They also have a lovely patio in back during the summer.

This was some of the worst Mexican food I've ever had.  It's pretty bad when your food comes out within minutes, you know they just had to have heated it up and not cooked it fresh.  Also, my boyfriend and I ordered different meals but it looked like the same thing just with different sauces on it.  The margarita was extremely watered down and had no flavor.  This place has been featured on Check Please, but I do not recommend it.

The Amish chicken enchiladas (definitely get the mole sauce) was ridiculously good. The refired beans as the side, yum. Margarita was the perfect balance of flavor and kick. Guacamole is the best we've had in a long time. Go here, its worth the wait. Just try to get a table in the front for better ambiance.

I have almost always had a great experience here.  They pay close attention to quality it seems.  The portions aren't as big as some other mexican restaurants, but the food is really excellent.  The tables are kind of close together which can make you feel crowded if they are crowded.  If they are not too busy they always seem to leave a table between you and the next group which is always nice.  I would definitely recommend it if you are savvy to the other mexican-american restaurants in town.
This place is looks deceivingly mediocre from the street, but it's really delicious. Get the slow cooked chipotle pork! And a big margarita.
One of my favorite Mexican restaurants in Chicago. The guacamole and chicken mole entree are two of my favorites. Nice patio in back for the summer months.

This is one of the top Mexican Restaurants in Chicago. The waiters are willing to give suggestions if you are undecided on what to order.  The salmon dish is exceptionally good and the pomegranate margarita is a must have.

Authentic Mexican food place in Lakeview.  This is not your typical burrito joint.  Pretty good for a date. For an appetizer try their quesadillas.  The enchiladas and fajitas are really good.  On Tuesdays Margaritas are half price.
The food was quite blend but the margaritas were very good and reasonably priced

This is a very small, but delicious Mexican restaurant. It is always busy and the atmopshere is great. The only caveat is that the tables are very close together, but you will forget about that after your meal!
Great Mexican food in the neighborhood. The staff is always friendly. They always remember you when you come in. The margarita's are especially good!
Mexican food elevated, you can taste the difference in the prep/ingredients. Great place to take a date!
The best mexican! Amazing margaritas. And the best salsa in Chicago! Great staff as well

In a city full of Mexican restaurants, El Nuevo Mexicano keeps me coming back.  The staff is so friendly in this family owned restaurant.  They remember you when you come back and celebrating your birthday there is definitely worth it.  Get a pomegranate margarita and the plantain echilladas with mole.  So great!!
Very cool place. LIttle small so you may have to wait if you don't make a reservation but overall the food is really qood and so are the margaritas!
Great food, great margaritas. Not too spacious, if you are with a big party, your best bet is outside. Cute little patio.

This is by far my favorite Mexico restaurant in Chicago. The food and service are excellent. The salmon dishes and the fajitas are my two go-tos, I find it hard to stray from those. It's quite small so a rez is a good idea.

Food and drinks are very good, in fact they have what I consider to be the best strawberry margarita ever, they use real strawberries. The service on the other hand is absent minded and lackluster. We had to ask the hostess more then once to find our server. But the food is good enough to make up for it.

This is a great restaurant with delicious food.  Yes, the food may be more expensive than your average run of the mill Mexican restaurant like Uncle Julios but that is because the meat is free range.  They have a fairly extensive vegan menu and great margaritas.
Service= LOVE IT!!! Thanks for the server I got. Food really good, I would go again. I was impressed overall with everything. Thank you.

I was thoroughly impressed.  The cuisine was delicious and portions were generous.  A great place for a first date, especially after visiting lincoln park zoo as it is well within walking distance.  For the environment service and cuisine its affordability was impressive.  We were checked on regularly as far as service, and they deserved every bit of the tip me and my date gave them.  Five Stars!
Food was fair service was poor

The food is good, above average, but when you pay $26 per mexican food plate, it is a bit expensive no matter how great it is. And it was not amazing. Service is terrible. We got our entree fish BEFORE we got free chips and salsa- those came last, and before we got our appetizer and drinks. Never going back.
